&lt;p&gt;Senior Clinical Fellow&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Paediatrics at Barnet Hospital&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Full Time - fixed term 6 months&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A Trust Senior Clinical Fellow in Paediatrics ST4+ level is required by Barnet Hospital (Royal Free London NHS Foundation Trust) commencing approximately December 2020 for 6 months. Previous experience is essential&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This post is to support the middle-grade rota. The post-holder will be part of a one in 8 rota to cover mainly general paediatrics with some support for the neonatal rota.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This post will be ideal for anyone with Paediatric experience who is looking to develop their clinical experience as a middle grade doctor. Experiences offered include regular general paediatric clinics, paediatric ED and inpatient care as well as neonatal intensive care.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;There will also be lots of opportunities for developing leadership and management competencies.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Name: Laila Hamidi Manesh&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Job title: Consultant&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Email address: lhamidi-manesh@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
